---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Maria Aise | AI/ML for Financial Risk & Reasoning Systems"
  description="AI/ML for financial risk, reasoning systems, and high-stakes decision modelling."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-kicker">AI / ML · Financial Risk · Reasoning</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        AI/ML for financial risk, reasoning systems, and high-stakes decisions.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-lead">
        Applied and research work spanning anomaly detection, multi-step
        reasoning architectures, non-stationary evaluation, and executive-grade
        decision intelligence.
      </p>
      <p class="hero-meta">
        PhD in AI/ML · Fellow CPA Australia · 20+ years across analytics,
        finance, and modelling. Focused on systems where error tolerance is low
        and explanations matter.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="hero-side">
      <div class="pill">Currently focused</div>
      <ul class="hero-list">
        <li>• Reasoning over P&amp;L and variance structures</li>
        <li>• Evaluation of ML under regime shifts</li>
        <li>• Decision interfaces for CFOs and risk committees</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="text-muted">
        Recent work: financial anomaly reasoner prototypes, volatility-aware
        evaluation frameworks, and decision layers translating model outputs
        into next actions.
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- CORE WORK AREAS -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Core Work Areas</h2>
      <div class="section-note">What I actually build and study</div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid-two">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Financial anomaly detection &amp; reasoning</div>
        <p class="card-body">
          Models that detect and explain anomalies in P&amp;L, balance sheets,
          and variance reports, pairing numeric signals with structured reasoning
          traces suitable for senior finance audiences.
        </p>
        <div class="chip-row">
          <span class="chip">P&amp;L anomalies</span>
          <span class="chip">Variance analysis</span>
          <span class="chip">Structured reasoning</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Non-stationary &amp; regime-shift evaluation</div>
        <p class="card-body">
          Evaluation frameworks for ML models under drift and structural breaks,
          common in markets and corporate performance data. Emphasis on robustness
          and failure-mode mapping.
        </p>
        <div class="chip-row">
          <span class="chip">Distribution shift</span>
          <span class="chip">Stress testing</span>
          <span class="chip">Risk metrics</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Reasoning architectures</div>
        <p class="card-body">
          Multi-step reasoning setups that combine synthetic tasks, constrained
          tool use, and evaluation protocols for finance- and governance-oriented
          decision problems.
        </p>
        <div class="chip-row">
          <span class="chip">Synthetic tasks</span>
          <span class="chip">Tool-augmented reasoning</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Decision systems for executives</div>
        <p class="card-body">
          Abstractions that convert model outputs into CFO- and board-level
          options, with clear tradeoffs and next-step actions rather than raw
          predictions.
        </p>
        <div class="chip-row">
          <span class="chip">Decision intelligence</span>
          <span class="chip">CFO interfaces</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SELECTED PROJECTS -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Selected Projects</h2>
      <div class="section-note">
        Concise summaries · details on <a href="/projects">Projects</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid-two">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Financial Anomaly Reasoner (prototype)</div>
        <div class="card-sub">
          Multi-step explanations for anomalies in P&amp;L and variance reports.
        </div>
        <p class="card-body">
          Pairs structured financial data with generated reasoning traces that
          identify where the anomaly is, which expectations it violates, and
          which drivers should be tested next. Designed to plug into CFO and
          controller workflows.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">
          Non-Stationary Risk Evaluation Framework
        </div>
        <div class="card-sub">
          Stress-testing models against drift and structural breaks.
        </div>
        <p class="card-body">
          Evaluation harness for classification/regression models under regime
          changes, using volatility-aware splits, drift detection, and
          risk-weighted metrics relevant to finance and corporate planning.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Executive Decision Modelling Layer</div>
        <div class="card-sub">
          From model outputs to options, not scores.
        </div>
        <p class="card-body">
          A light abstraction over ML services that turns predictions into
          scenarios, tradeoffs, and recommended actions, focused on reporting,
          budgeting, and risk review cycles.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Reasoning Benchmarks for Finance Tasks</div>
        <div class="card-sub">
          Task set for evaluating step-wise reasoning on financial questions.
        </div>
        <p class="card-body">
          Prototype benchmark of structured tasks (variance explanations,
          reconciliation checks, policy-constrained decisions) used to measure
          model reasoning quality beyond single-shot answers.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SIGNALS / LINKS OUT -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Signals</h2>
      <div class="section-note">Where to look next</div>
    </div>

    <ul class="list-compact">
      <li>
        Research and preprints: <a href="/research">/research</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        System and project details: <a href="/projects">/projects</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        Technical notes and memos: <a href="/writing">/writing</a> and
        <a href="/blog">/blog</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
